---
import Layout from "../layouts/Layout.astro";
import resume from "../data/resume.json";

const { basics } = resume;
---

<Layout title={`${basics.name} — Interests`}>
  <main class="mx-auto max-w-2xl px-6 py-12">
    <nav class="mb-6 text-sm text-slate-500 dark:text-slate-400">
      <a href="/" class="transition hover:text-slate-900 dark:hover:text-slate-100">← Home</a>
    </nav>

    <header>
      <h1 class="text-3xl font-bold tracking-tight sm:text-4xl">Interests</h1>
      <p class="mt-3 max-w-prose text-base leading-relaxed text-slate-700 dark:text-slate-300">
        Things I do when I'm not coding — mostly excuses to share time with people,
        and the occasional rabbit hole I follow alone.
      </p>
    </header>

    <div class="mt-10 space-y-8">
      <article class="flex gap-4 sm:gap-5">
        <div class="flex h-10 w-10 shrink-0 items-center justify-center rounded-md bg-slate-100 text-slate-600 dark:bg-slate-800 dark:text-slate-300">
          <svg viewBox="0 0 24 24" width="20" height="20" fill="none" stroke="currentColor" stroke-width="2" stroke-linecap="round" stroke-linejoin="round" aria-hidden="true">
            <polyline points="22 12 18 12 15 21 9 3 6 12 2 12"></polyline>
          </svg>
        </div>
        <div class="min-w-0 flex-1">
          <h2 class="text-base font-semibold text-slate-900 dark:text-slate-100">Running</h2>
          <p class="mt-2 max-w-prose text-sm leading-relaxed text-slate-700 dark:text-slate-300">
            I run to clear my head and stay consistent more than to chase PRs.
            I like to have at least one map drawing for every place I visit, and I share those on
            {" "}<a
              href="https://www.strava.com/athletes/michaelrbk"
              class="underline decoration-slate-400 underline-offset-4 transition hover:decoration-slate-900 dark:hover:decoration-slate-100"
            >Strava</a>{" "}
            if you're curious.
          </p>
        </div>
      </article>

      <article class="flex gap-4 sm:gap-5">
        <div class="flex h-10 w-10 shrink-0 items-center justify-center rounded-md bg-slate-100 text-slate-600 dark:bg-slate-800 dark:text-slate-300">
          <svg viewBox="0 0 24 24" width="20" height="20" fill="none" stroke="currentColor" stroke-width="2" stroke-linecap="round" stroke-linejoin="round" aria-hidden="true">
            <path d="M2 3h6a4 4 0 0 1 4 4v14a3 3 0 0 0-3-3H2z"></path>
            <path d="M22 3h-6a4 4 0 0 0-4 4v14a3 3 0 0 1 3-3h7z"></path>
          </svg>
        </div>
        <div class="min-w-0 flex-1">
          <h2 class="text-base font-semibold text-slate-900 dark:text-slate-100">Reading</h2>
          <p class="mt-2 max-w-prose text-sm leading-relaxed text-slate-700 dark:text-slate-300">
            Currently working through Cormac McCarthy's <em>Blood Meridian</em>.
            Bernard Cornwell anchors the historical-fiction side — I've followed
            his Saxon Stories all the way, plus the Arthurian and
            Sharpe arcs. Sci-fi fills the other half: Le Guin, Gibson, Bradbury,
            the Strugatskys, and the occasional contemporary like Andy Weir.
            Brazilian literature shows up regularly too — Machado de Assis,
            Itamar Vieira Junior.
          </p>
        </div>
      </article>

      <article class="flex gap-4 sm:gap-5">
        <div class="flex h-10 w-10 shrink-0 items-center justify-center rounded-md bg-slate-100 text-slate-600 dark:bg-slate-800 dark:text-slate-300">
          <svg viewBox="0 0 24 24" width="20" height="20" fill="none" stroke="currentColor" stroke-width="2" stroke-linecap="round" stroke-linejoin="round" aria-hidden="true">
            <rect x="3" y="3" width="18" height="18" rx="2"></rect>
            <path d="M3 12h18"></path>
            <path d="M12 3v18"></path>
          </svg>
        </div>
        <div class="min-w-0 flex-1">
          <h2 class="text-base font-semibold text-slate-900 dark:text-slate-100">Graphic novels</h2>
          <p class="mt-2 max-w-prose text-sm leading-relaxed text-slate-700 dark:text-slate-300">
            Comics share equal shelf space with prose, and I tend toward the
            literary, international end of the spectrum. Standouts: Spiegelman's
            <em>Maus</em>, Satrapi's <em>Persépolis</em>, Oesterheld &amp; Solano
            López's <em>O Eternauta</em>, Gaiman's <em>Sandman</em>, Gabriel Bá's
            <em>Two Brothers</em>, and Chaboute's <em>Alone</em>.
          </p>
        </div>
      </article>

      <article class="flex gap-4 sm:gap-5">
        <div class="flex h-10 w-10 shrink-0 items-center justify-center rounded-md bg-slate-100 text-slate-600 dark:bg-slate-800 dark:text-slate-300">
          <svg viewBox="0 0 24 24" width="20" height="20" fill="none" stroke="currentColor" stroke-width="2" stroke-linecap="round" stroke-linejoin="round" aria-hidden="true">
            <line x1="6" y1="11" x2="10" y2="11"></line>
            <line x1="8" y1="9" x2="8" y2="13"></line>
            <line x1="15" y1="12" x2="15.01" y2="12"></line>
            <line x1="18" y1="10" x2="18.01" y2="10"></line>
            <path d="M17.32 5H6.68a4 4 0 0 0-3.978 3.59c-.006.052-.01.101-.017.152C2.604 9.416 2 14.456 2 16a3 3 0 0 0 3 3c1 0 1.5-.5 2-1l1.414-1.414A2 2 0 0 1 9.828 16h4.344a2 2 0 0 1 1.414.586L17 18c.5.5 1 1 2 1a3 3 0 0 0 3-3c0-1.545-.604-6.584-.685-7.258A4 4 0 0 0 17.32 5z"></path>
          </svg>
        </div>
        <div class="min-w-0 flex-1">
          <h2 class="text-base font-semibold text-slate-900 dark:text-slate-100">
            PC co-op with friends
          </h2>
          <p class="mt-2 max-w-prose text-sm leading-relaxed text-slate-700 dark:text-slate-300">
            Deep Rock Galactic and Hunt: Showdown are the regular rotation —
            I'm in it for the squad more than the genre. Rock and Stone. Library on
            {" "}<a
              href="https://steamcommunity.com/id/michaelrbk/"
              class="underline decoration-slate-400 underline-offset-4 transition hover:decoration-slate-900 dark:hover:decoration-slate-100"
            >Steam</a>.
          </p>
        </div>
      </article>

      <article class="flex gap-4 sm:gap-5">
        <div class="flex h-10 w-10 shrink-0 items-center justify-center rounded-md bg-slate-100 text-slate-600 dark:bg-slate-800 dark:text-slate-300">
          <svg viewBox="0 0 24 24" width="20" height="20" fill="none" stroke="currentColor" stroke-width="2" stroke-linecap="round" stroke-linejoin="round" aria-hidden="true">
            <rect x="3" y="3" width="18" height="18" rx="2"></rect>
            <path d="M16 8h.01"></path>
            <path d="M8 8h.01"></path>
            <path d="M8 16h.01"></path>
            <path d="M16 16h.01"></path>
            <path d="M12 12h.01"></path>
          </svg>
        </div>
        <div class="min-w-0 flex-1">
          <h2 class="text-base font-semibold text-slate-900 dark:text-slate-100">
            Board games &amp; Arkham Horror LCG
          </h2>
          <p class="mt-2 max-w-prose text-sm leading-relaxed text-slate-700 dark:text-slate-300">
            I'll try almost any board game, but the Arkham Horror Card Game is the
            obsession — long-running campaigns where the story actually remembers
            what you did. Collection on
            {" "}<a
              href="https://boardgamegeek.com/profile/michaelrbk"
              class="underline decoration-slate-400 underline-offset-4 transition hover:decoration-slate-900 dark:hover:decoration-slate-100"
            >BoardGameGeek</a>.
          </p>
        </div>
      </article>

      <article class="flex gap-4 sm:gap-5">
        <div class="flex h-10 w-10 shrink-0 items-center justify-center rounded-md bg-slate-100 text-slate-600 dark:bg-slate-800 dark:text-slate-300">
          <svg viewBox="0 0 24 24" width="20" height="20" fill="none" stroke="currentColor" stroke-width="2" stroke-linecap="round" stroke-linejoin="round" aria-hidden="true">
            <path d="M22 20v-9H2v9a2 2 0 0 0 2 2h16a2 2 0 0 0 2-2Z"></path>
            <path d="M18 11V4H6v7"></path>
            <path d="M15 22v-4a3 3 0 0 0-3-3a3 3 0 0 0-3 3v4"></path>
            <path d="M22 11V9"></path>
            <path d="M2 11V9"></path>
            <path d="M6 4V2"></path>
            <path d="M18 4V2"></path>
            <path d="M10 4V2"></path>
            <path d="M14 4V2"></path>
          </svg>
        </div>
        <div class="min-w-0 flex-1">
          <h2 class="text-base font-semibold text-slate-900 dark:text-slate-100">Chess</h2>
          <p class="mt-2 max-w-prose text-sm leading-relaxed text-slate-700 dark:text-slate-300">
            Comes and goes in waves — when I want a different kind of puzzle
            from code. Mostly online on
            {" "}<a
              href="https://www.chess.com/member/michaelrbk"
              class="underline decoration-slate-400 underline-offset-4 transition hover:decoration-slate-900 dark:hover:decoration-slate-100"
            >chess.com</a>.
          </p>
        </div>
      </article>

      <article class="flex gap-4 sm:gap-5">
        <div class="flex h-10 w-10 shrink-0 items-center justify-center rounded-md bg-slate-100 text-slate-600 dark:bg-slate-800 dark:text-slate-300">
          <svg viewBox="0 0 24 24" width="20" height="20" fill="none" stroke="currentColor" stroke-width="2" stroke-linecap="round" stroke-linejoin="round" aria-hidden="true">
            <circle cx="12" cy="6" r="3"></circle>
            <path d="M12 9v7"></path>
            <path d="M6 20h12l-2-4H8z"></path>
          </svg>
        </div>
        <div class="min-w-0 flex-1">
          <h2 class="text-base font-semibold text-slate-900 dark:text-slate-100">
            Retro &amp; fantasy console coding
          </h2>
          <p class="mt-2 max-w-prose text-sm leading-relaxed text-slate-700 dark:text-slate-300">
            Grew up with retro games and still keep coming back to them. Lately
            that means making tiny things on
            {" "}<a
              href="https://tic80.com/"
              class="underline decoration-slate-400 underline-offset-4 transition hover:decoration-slate-900 dark:hover:decoration-slate-100"
            >TIC-80</a>{" "}
             and
            {" "}<a
              href="https://www.lexaloffle.com/pico-8.php"
              class="underline decoration-slate-400 underline-offset-4 transition hover:decoration-sla
te-900 dark:hover:decoration-slate-100"
            >PICO-8</a>
            — here's a
            {" "}<a
              href="https://github.com/michaelrbk/tic_snake"
              class="underline decoration-slate-400 underline-offset-4 transition hover:decoration-slate-900 dark:hover:decoration-slate-100"
            >Snake clone</a>{" "}
            I wrote in Lua for TIC-80.
          </p>
        </div>
      </article>
    </div>
  </main>
</Layout>
